title: A1425 no keyboard trackpad or fan spin.
message:
I have an A1425 retina not sure the exact board model number yet, (have not pulled it out the case yet).
It powers on fine and runs everything, except i have no fan spin (tested with a working one)  and also no keyboard or trackpad,  i tried testing with another keyboard but it didn't work. is there any common components for theses issues or am i going to need to track it down between each line?

Thanks

title: A1425 no keyboard trackpad or fan spin.
message: A1425 has 2 fans, are we sure we are talking about an A1425 here?

title: A1425 no keyboard trackpad or fan spin.
message: yeah your right,  someone set a diff retina cover on it.  it is a A1502 board number 820-4924 A

title: A1425 no keyboard trackpad or fan spin.
message: 4924 does NOT spin the fan until the CPU gets warmer. Try another trackpad flex/trackpad in general cable is super common failure point on 4924
